@node BAZAA "Bazaar of Baghdad"

@{b}Bazaar of Baghdad@{ub}

Rarity  = AN(U3)
Type    = Land
Artist  = Jeff A. Menges

Text(AN): Tap to take two cards from your library, after which you must
          immediately discard three from your hand to your graveyard. If
          you don't have three or more cards in your hand, discard your
          whole hand. No spells may be cast between drawing and discarding
          cards.

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_B.guide/BAZAA}

@endnode
@node CITYO "City of Brass"

@{b}City of Brass@{ub}

Rarity  = AN(U3) / CR(U1)
Type    = Land
Artist  = Mark Tedin

Text(CR): Whenever City of Brass becomes tapped, it deals 1 damage to you.
          <T>: Add one mana of any color to your mana pool.

Text(AN): Tap to add 1 mana of any color to your mana pool. You suffer 1
          damage whenever City of Brass becomes tapped.

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_C.guide/CBRAS}

@endnode
@node DESER "Desert"

@{b}Desert@{ub}

Rarity  = AN(C11)
Type    = Land
Artist  = Jesper Myfors

Text(AN): Tap to add 1 colorless mana to your mana pool OR do 1 damage to
          an attacking creature after it deals its damage.

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_D.guide/DESER}

@endnode
@node DIAMO "Diamond Valley"

@{b}Diamond Valley@{ub}

Rarity  = AN(U2)
Type    = Land
Artist  = Brian Snoddy

Text(AN): Tap to sacrifice one of your creatures in exchange for a number
          of life points equal to its toughness. Note that this ability
          may be used after blocking has been declared.

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_D.guide/DIAMO}

@endnode
@node ELEPH "Elephant Graveyard"

@{b}Elephant Graveyard@{ub}

Rarity  = AN(U2)
Type    = Land
Artist  = Rob Alexander

Text(AN): Tap to add 1 colorless mana to your mana pool or regenerate an
          Elephant or Mammoth.

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_E.guide/ELEPH}

@endnode
@node ISLAN "Island of Wak-Wak"

@{b}Island of Wak-Wak@{ub}

Rarity  = AN(U2)
Type    = Land
Artist  = Douglas Shuler

Text(AN): Tap to reduce target flying creature's power to 0.

Flavor Text: @{i}The Isle of Wak-Wak, home to a tribe of winged folk, is
             named for a peculiar fruit that grows there. The fruit
             looks like a woman's head, and when ripe speaks the word
             "Wak".@{ui}

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_I.guide/ISWAK}

@endnode
@node LIBRA "Library of Alexandria"

@{b}Library of Alexandria@{ub}

Rarity  = AN(U3)
Type    = Land
Artist  = Mark Poole

Text(AN): Tap to add 1 colorless mana to your mana pool OR draw a card from
          your library; you may use the card drawing ability only if you
          have exactly seven cards in your hand.

 @{" Rulings " link MTG_CARD_L.guide/LIBAL}

@endnode
